The paper deals with optimizing multiway equijoins on relational tables, which is a problem in database systems (cs.DB). The use of degree information to bound the output size of a query and obtain faster join algorithms involves graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS, cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of MapReduce for parallel processing (cs.CC) and the optimization of communication complexity (cs.SI).
